It CITES its methods rather than reproducing them:
  - The EARS (Easy Approach to Requirements Syntax) patterns are credited to
    Alistair Mavin et al. (2009) and are described here in original wording, not copied
    from the IEEE conference paper.
  - Requirement quality and verification guidance aligns with NASA public-domain
    systems-engineering guidance (NPR 7123.1 / NASA SE Handbook).
  - This pack is NOT a reproduction of ISO/IEC/IEEE 29148, the INCOSE Guide for Writing
    Requirements, or any other copyrighted standard. For the authoritative text, consult
    those sources directly.

